	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 24th 5:10 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Although it supposedly drops from Lesser Icebone Skeletons, I didn't see a wand drop off them and I accumulated more than 8 stacks of bone chips from beating them up.&nbsp;&nbsp;Camp in the room north of where the Jester spawns, kill the spawn in there (it's a lesser icebone about 1/3 of the time) and all the spawns in nearby room as well as the area where the Forager wanders (as marked on EQatlas's map).  That's the best place I've seen for Lesser icebones.  For a wiz, almost everything in here (except Lesser Ice/Charbone and burynai Sappers) dies to the lv39 Lightning shock.  Go nuts wandering the halls killing the capital-E Excavators after you kill everything near the jester area.  I eventually got the wand (after 4 days camping here) off an Excavator sort-of near the stairs to the main level.  At lv49, Sappers agro on me, as will all undead if I don't have invis undead up.  Supposedly, Lesser Icebones that have the wand on them will be holding it when they are standing around.  The Excavators do NOT ever look like they're holding anything, even when they are.  The one that dropped the wand did not have it visibly equipped, it was just in inventory (icon looks like a Weeping wand, small bluish-grey).  <br><br>Wand is NOT insta-click.  5 second cast time, must be equipped to use.  It's not boosted by any Improved Damage items or Spell Haste items that I can tell.<br><br>If the drop rate has been increased, I can't tell.  I easily killed a few hundred Excavators and just as many Lesser Icebones over 4 days before it dropped.<br><br>FYI, it's the only unlimited-charge DD item usable by wizards until lv51 (when you can get the Thurg/Kael/Skyshrine quest robe).  It drastically boosts a wizard's damage output at any level after 12, turning all your unused time into Nuking time.  Also handy for finishing off a running mob instead of wasting a nuke on them.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
